A unique string used to identify the given. This string can
contain letters (a–z; A–Z), numbers (0–9), dashes (-), and underscores (_), with a
maximum of 100 characters

Dip is the steepest angle of descent of the fault plane relative to a horizontal plane;
it is measured in degrees [0,90]

Minimum value of magnitude representing the mid
point of the first magnitude bin
Annual number of earthquakes for each magnitude bin
Rake angle (specified following the Aki-Richards convention; see Aki and Richards, (2002)) [degrees]

The strike direction correspond to the angle between the north and the direction you
take so that when you walk along the fault trace the fault dips on your right.

dip is the steepest angle of descent of the fault plane relative to a horizontal plane;
it is measured in degrees [0,90]

the direction in which a hanging wall block moves during a rupture,
measured relative to fault strike on the plane of the fault
